headline: Walmart to Cut Around 1,500 Corporate Jobs in Restructuring Drive
summary: On May 21, Walmart Inc. (NYSE:WMT) announced plans to cut ~1,500 corporate jobs as part of a restructuring effort aimed at increasing efficiency, speeding up decision-making, and simplifying its organizational structure. The layoffs will primarily affect only corporate employees and not store associates across its Global Tech team, advertising business (Walmart Connect), and e-commerce fulfillment […]

headline: Target's Market Share Is Slipping -- Time to Buy the Dip or Stay Away?
summary: Target has been losing market share to its retail rivals.  Meanwhile, it just reported poor Q1 results and lowered its full-year guidance.  While its stock managed to rise following its fiscal first-quarter earnings report last week, there was not much to cheer about with Target's (NYSE: TGT) latest results.
